{
  "texts": [
    "A confusion matrix is one such performance evaluation tool popularly adopted in machine learning, representing the accuracy of a classification model.",
    "It displays the number of true positives, true negatives, false positives, and false negatives.",
    "By calculating the TPR and TNR as in Equations 1, 2, this matrix aids in analyzing model performance and identifying misclassifications (Fawcett, 2006).",
    "The value TPR and TNR can be calculated using Equations 1, 2 respectively.",
    "TN (True Negative): The count of instances accurately classified by the model as belonging to the negative class, when they actually are in the negative class."
  ]
}